{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3225", "repo": "rails", "body": "Just looking through the code and noticed this:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nruby_rake_task \"assets:precompile:nondigest\" if Rails.application.config.assets.digest\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhile I understand that this does work (after some time working though the code), it looks backwards. Perhaps something like the following would be better:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nruby_rake_task \"assets:precompile:nondigest\"\r\nruby_rake_task \"assets:precompile:digest\" if Rails.application.config.assets.digest\r\n# order ensures that manifest will be overwritten if configured for digest\r\n```\r\n\r\nJust a thought.", "_id": {"$oid": "52383942bd3543c15101009d"}, "issue_id": 3225, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2307410", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3225#issuecomment-2307410", "updated_at": "2011-10-06T07:59:47Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb", "login": "thomasfedb", "gravatar_id": "aa1aefd297451de8c9992e3d52621804", "html_url": "https://github.com/thomasfedb", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/aa1aefd297451de8c9992e3d52621804?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2b644053f51096f77328548c15d942fb.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 193831, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thomasfedb/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-10-06